---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../lib/constants';

const title = `Legal Notice — ${SITE_NAME}`;
const description = `Legal notice for ${SITE_NAME}: publisher information, hosting details, intellectual property, privacy policy, GDPR rights, cookies, terms of use and liability disclaimer.`;
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} noIndex={true}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert mx-auto max-w-3xl">

      <h1>Legal Notice</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

      <p>
        In accordance with applicable consumer protection and digital services legislation, the following
        legal notice is provided to users and visitors of the website {SITE_URL}. By accessing and browsing
        this website, users acknowledge and accept these terms in their entirety.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Publisher Information</h2>
      <p>
        This website is published by:<br />
        <strong>Mottalib Radif</strong><br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a><br />
        Website: <a href={SITE_URL}>{SITE_URL}</a><br />
        Editor-in-Chief: Mottalib Radif
      </p>
      <p>
        The publisher assumes editorial responsibility for all content published on the website, with the
        exception of results generated by the paycheck calculators, which depend on data entered by the
        user and on federal and state tax parameters in effect at the date of consultation.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted by:<br />
        <strong>Vercel Inc.</strong><br />
        440 N Barranca Ave #4133, Covina, CA 91723, United States<br />
        Website: <a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">vercel.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Vercel is a cloud platform for static and serverless deployment. The infrastructure relies on a
        global edge network that serves pages from the server closest to each visitor. HTTPS is used to
        encrypt all data in transit. As a technical hosting provider, Vercel does not exercise editorial
        control over the website's content.
      </p>

      <h2>3. About This Website</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>{SITE_NAME}</strong> is an independent information platform offering free paycheck
        calculators and tax estimation tools for the United States. All calculations are performed locally
        in your browser using client-side JavaScript; no personal data is sent to our servers. The website
        provides informational content about federal income tax, state income tax, FICA (Social Security
        and Medicare), and other payroll deductions.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on {SITE_NAME}, including text, calculators, graphics, source code, calculation
        algorithms, page layouts and design elements, is protected by copyright and intellectual property
        laws. No reproduction, distribution, or modification of any part of this site is permitted without
        the prior written consent of the publisher, except as allowed by applicable fair use provisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Users are authorised to browse the website for strictly personal and private use. Brief quotations
        for informational purposes are permitted provided the source is credited.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} is committed to protecting your privacy. All calculations are performed entirely in
        your browser. We do not collect, store, or transmit any salary, tax, or financial data that you
        enter into our calculators. The technical architecture is designed according to the principle of
        "privacy by design".
      </p>
      <p>
        We use Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly analytics service that uses no cookies, stores no
        personal data, and is fully compliant with GDPR and CCPA. URL parameters (e.g., ?gross=60000&state=CA)
        serve solely to allow sharing and are not evaluated server-side. For full details, see our
        <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} uses <strong>no tracking cookies</strong>. No advertising, profiling, or third-party
        cookies are placed. User preferences (such as dark/light mode) are stored in the browser's
        localStorage, which is not a cookie and is never transmitted to our servers. Since no tracking
        cookies are used, a cookie consent banner is not legally required.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data Protection (GDPR / CCPA)</h2>
      <h3>7.1 Data Controller</h3>
      <p>
        The data controller for this website is Mottalib Radif, reachable at contact@truetakehomepay.com.
      </p>
      <h3>7.2 GDPR Rights (EU Users)</h3>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR, EU users have the following rights: right of access (Art. 15), right to
        rectification (Art. 16), right to erasure (Art. 17), right to restriction of processing (Art. 18),
        right to data portability (Art. 20), right to object (Art. 21), right to withdraw consent (Art. 7),
        and right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77).
      </p>
      <h3>7.3 CCPA Rights (California Residents)</h3>
      <p>
        Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), California residents have the right to: know what
        personal information is collected, request deletion of personal information, opt out of the sale of
        personal information, and not be discriminated against for exercising privacy rights. Since we do
        not collect personal information through our calculators, these rights are effectively exercised
        by default.
      </p>
      <h3>7.4 State Privacy Laws</h3>
      <p>
        We comply with applicable state privacy laws including the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act
        (VCDPA), Colorado Privacy Act (CPA), Connecticut Data Privacy Act (CTDPA), and Utah Consumer
        Privacy Act (UCPA).
      </p>
      <p>
        Since the website does not collect personal data, these rights are currently not applicable in
        practice. For any enquiry, contact us at contact@truetakehomepay.com.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Terms of Use</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing {SITE_URL}, you agree to these terms. The website is accessible free of charge. The
        publisher uses all reasonable means to ensure quality access but is under no obligation of result.
        Access may be interrupted at any time for maintenance or updates. Users agree to use the website
        in accordance with its intended purpose and not for unlawful purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Liability Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The calculators and information on {SITE_NAME} are provided for educational and informational
        purposes only. They do not constitute tax advice, financial advice, or any professional service.
        While we strive for accuracy, we make no warranties regarding the completeness or accuracy of any
        calculations or content. Users should consult a qualified CPA, tax professional, or financial
        advisor for advice specific to their circumstances.
      </p>
      <p>
        The publisher shall not be held liable for any direct or indirect damages resulting from the use
        of the calculators, information, or tools provided on this site, including data loss, service
        interruptions, or damages to user equipment.
      </p>

      <h2>10. External Links</h2>
      <p>
        This site may contain links to external websites, including IRS.gov, state tax authority websites,
        and other reference sources. The publisher has no control over the content of these external sites
        and disclaims all responsibility for their content, privacy practices, or availability.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Applicable Law</h2>
      <p>
        This legal notice is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States.
        Any disputes arising from the use of this website shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction
        of the courts of the United States. The potential invalidity of any clause shall not affect the
        remaining provisions.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes and Contact</h2>
      <p>
        The publisher reserves the right to modify this legal notice at any time. Changes take effect upon
        publication. For questions, contact us at:<br />
        <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
